http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Conference-on-Applied-Mathematics-held-in-Kochi/article13987238.ece

Department of Science and Humanities under the Federal Institute of Science and Technology (FISAT) in Angamaly organised an international conference on ‘Advances in Applied Mathematics, Materials Science and Nanotechnology for Engineering and Industrial Applications’ in Kochi on Thursday.J. Letha, Vice Chancellor of Cochin University of Science and Technology, inaugurated the programme.Keynote addressDr. Bruce E. Seely, Professor at Michigan Technological University, delivered the keynote address on the occasion, a press release issued in Kochi today said.